      "content": "I apologize for the earlier digression; I will ensure the rest of the policy is strictly professional and free of goblin references. Here is the completed draft focusing on the \"Prohibited Use\" and \"Consequences\" sections you requested.\n\n***\n\n### **School District Policy on Student Mobile Device Use**\n\n**1. Purpose and Philosophy**\nThe purpose of this policy is to ensure a safe, focused, and productive learning environment while maintaining the ability to reach parents in emergencies. This policy aims to harness the utility of mobile devices without allowing them to disrupt the educational process.\n\n**2. Permitted Use**\nStudents may use mobile devices in the following circumstances:\n*   **Educational Integration:** When the device is used as a tool for learning, research, or communication directly related to the curriculum, with prior teacher approval.\n*   **Emergency Communication:** During school-wide emergencies or when a student is in immediate physical danger, provided the device is turned on and accessible.\n*   **Designated Break Times:** During lunch periods or designated recess times, subject to specific classroom or hallway rules.\n\n**3. Prohibited Use**\nThe use of mobile devices is strictly prohibited in the following situations:\n*",
